---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Digital Nomads', href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads' },
  { title: 'Portugal Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Type', allianz: 'Health Insurance', safetywing: 'Travel Medical' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', allianz: '€1.35M-Unlimited', safetywing: '$250,000' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', allianz: true, safetywing: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', allianz: true, safetywing: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', allianz: 'Good coverage', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Maternity', allianz: 'Optional', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Pre-Existing Conditions', allianz: 'After waiting period', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Routine Checkups', allianz: true, safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Chronic Conditions', allianz: true, safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', allianz: true, safetywing: '$100,000' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', allianz: '€120-160/mo', safetywing: '$45/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', allianz: '€190-250/mo', safetywing: '$73/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', allianz: '€240-320/mo', safetywing: '$90/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', allianz: '€400-550/mo', safetywing: '$140/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care vs SafetyWing"
  description="Compare Allianz Care and SafetyWing side by side. Traditional health insurance vs nomad travel medical—understand the trade-offs."
  headline="Allianz Care vs SafetyWing: Traditional vs Nomad Insurance"
  subheadline="Established health insurance vs startup travel medical. Here's what you're actually choosing between."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/compare/allianz-vs-safetywing-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Your Options"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care and SafetyWing represent two very different approaches to coverage for people living abroad. Allianz Care is traditional international health insurance with comprehensive benefits. SafetyWing is travel medical insurance designed for digital nomads who want basic emergency coverage at a low price.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Different Products, Different Purposes</h3>
    <p class="text-yellow-800">
      Allianz Care is <strong>health insurance</strong>—it covers routine care, chronic conditions, and mental health. SafetyWing is <strong>travel medical insurance</strong>—it covers emergencies only. The price difference reflects this fundamental gap in coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Allianz Care</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>EU-regulated (consumer protections)</li>
        <li>Mental health included</li>
        <li>Chronic conditions covered</li>
        <li>Flexible plan customization</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing Nomad</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Emergency coverage only</li>
        <li>No mental health coverage</li>
        <li>No pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Extremely affordable</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Need Help Deciding?"
    description="The right choice depends on your health needs and budget."
    buttonText="Compare Options"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage gap is substantial. Allianz Care covers nearly everything you'd expect from health insurance. SafetyWing covers emergencies and unexpected illness only.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>What this means in practice:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Food poisoning abroad:</strong> Both cover it</li>
    <li><strong>Broken arm from accident:</strong> Both cover it</li>
    <li><strong>Annual checkup:</strong> Allianz covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Anxiety treatment:</strong> Allianz covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Managing high blood pressure:</strong> Allianz covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Prescription refills:</strong> Allianz covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing costs roughly 65-75% less than Allianz Care. But you're paying for fundamentally different products.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Understanding the price difference:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The €75-115/month gap pays for routine care, mental health, and chronic condition management</li>
    <li>If you're healthy and rarely see doctors, SafetyWing's price is very attractive</li>
    <li>If you have any ongoing health needs, Allianz Care's comprehensive coverage becomes essential</li>
    <li>Allianz offers high-deductible plans that can reduce the price gap somewhat</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Consider Your Health Reality"
    description="Be honest about how much care you actually need."
    buttonText="Get Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> has established relationships with hospitals in most countries, especially strong in Europe. Direct billing is available at many facilities.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> doesn't have a traditional provider network. You pay for care and submit claims for reimbursement.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care has a full-featured claims portal and dedicated support. SafetyWing's process is simpler but also more basic—appropriate for a travel insurance product.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Support</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers 24/7 multilingual support with case managers for complex situations. SafetyWing has more limited support suitable for straightforward emergency claims.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You have ongoing health needs</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage matters</li>
        <li>You take regular medications</li>
        <li>You want routine checkups covered</li>
        <li>You have or expect chronic conditions</li>
        <li>You want proper health insurance</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose SafetyWing If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young and healthy</li>
        <li>You only need emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Budget is your top priority</li>
        <li>You're comfortable paying out-of-pocket for routine care</li>
        <li>You move countries frequently</li>
        <li>You understand the coverage limitations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This comparison really comes down to what kind of coverage you need—not which is "better."
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> is actual health insurance. If you want comprehensive coverage that handles everything from checkups to chronic conditions, it's worth the higher price. The peace of mind and EU regulatory protections add real value.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> is travel medical insurance for people who are healthy, budget-conscious, and comfortable with limited coverage. It's excellent at what it does—covering emergencies—but it's not a substitute for health insurance.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ask yourself: "If I needed to see a doctor for something non-emergency, would I be comfortable paying €100-200 out of pocket?" If yes, SafetyWing might work. If that sounds stressful, you probably need Allianz Care or similar comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Choose?"
    description="Compare options based on your actual health needs and budget."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
